In automatic mode, will output true if the filename of the loaded checkpoint contains 'XL' (case insensitive), otherwise will output 'false'.
In manual, will output the value of the second widget.
This influences the function of some nodes wherever some modification is needed for XL checkpoints like using a secondary sampler with a refiner

When using an SDXL-based checkpoint, set 1 will be forced. Those are the values that SDXL has been trained on, so they're the best fit for it.

You can freely add new presets. The first 2 numbers in each line are used (1st- width, 2nd - height. You can write anything after that, and anything that isn't a number before and between the two numbers.

To add sets, you need to convert to nodes, copy one of the set nodes and connect it's output to the text list node. If you run out of connections, use a text list concatenate node

The selected preset is concatenated in front of the main prompt

When adding new presets, they should be separated by a "#" character
The preset text should begin any number of new lines below. The line with '#' and all subsequent empty lines are removed before combining with the main prompt

A relatively simple workflow for generating basic images, with some QoL spruced in.

Main feature is seamless transition between using SD1.5 and SDXL-based models. All you need to do is switch the model and as long as it contains "XL" (case insensitive) in the filename, everything that would need to be switched is automated. How exactly is explained in notes next to the relevant nodes.

When using SDXL-base checkpoints, the generation process in each pass will be split between 2 KSamplers, with the second one running the refiner. The 'base to refiner ratio' widget controls the % of the set steps done by the refiner. It may be a good idea to increase it (so the refiner does more) in the second pass, especially with low denoising.

Detects faces, crops them, samples at a high resolution, downscales and pastes in. Each face is processed separately

 Bbox detects a rectangle around a face
 SAM detects skin
 The SAM-detected mask is cropped within Bbox mask
* threshold: Detect only those object whose recognized confidence is above this set value.
* dilation: Expand the detected mask area.
* guide_size: This feature attempt detail recovery only when the size of the detected mask is smaller than this value. If the size is larger, this feature increase the resolution and attempt detail recovery.
* guide_size_for: This parameter determines whether guide_size is used based on the size of the detected face (bbox) or the size of the crop area that includes the face and is broadly cropped by crop_factor.
* max_size: The guide_size increases the scale so that the shorter side reaches the guide_size. For masks with elongated shapes, this can cause a significant scale up. The max_size limits the maximum size of one side.
* feather: When compositing the recovered details onto the original image, this feature use a gradient to composite it so that the boundaries are not visible. The thickness of this gradient is determined.
* force_inpaint: force_inpaint will try to force regeneration even if it is smaller than guide_size . This function is useful when you simply want to change to another type of prompt other than the function to save details. However, in this case, upscale is forcibly fixed to 1.
* Cycle: will repeat sampling of each face this many times
* Change Prompt: if true, will discard passed prompt and use the prompt provided in this node. Keeps passed LoRA models.
* LoRA: LoRA models added in this node are only for the purposes of the detailer. They are not included in the ouput pipes

DOES NOT WORK FOR 2D IMAGES (MUST BE SUFFICCIENTLY REALISTIC)

Modified versions of some nodes for customizablity

AYS - AlignYourSteps scheduler.
Since comfyui makes it a require a separate node for some reason, I couldn't make it into 1 group node so it is separated into it's own node.
There are 3 schedulers: for SD1, SDXL, and SDV, the correct one is chosen automatically based on xl? input.
They are very fast and good quality, I've been running just 10 steps, but could possibly go lower
